Joburg-based fine artist and sculptor Azael Langa is extending his creative juices outside the boarders of Mzansi. The TUT graduate in Fine and Applied Arts will be showcasing in Zurich, Switzerland on 13 December. “It’s a good feeling to get to learn more about other people and their cultures. I'll learn more about my career as well,” he says. He added that this exhibition reflects the aesthetics of being an African appreciate other artistic elements in Europe. “My work has always been an interpretation of my everyday life, and also shows our African way of life,” he said. 